Package com.CZ2002.interfaces

Interface IMainManager

All Known Implementing Classes:
RestaurantManager
public interface IMainManager
This interface provides an access point to all other Manager classes within the Restaurant.

Implementations of this interface should provide some way of retrieving a particular Manager through getSubManager(String manager, Class<? extends T> type).

  • Field Details

    • subManagers

      static final HashMap<String,Manager<?>> subManagers
      The storage point of all Manager classes within the Restaurant.

      As Manager classes are stored in a HashMap, they can be added and removed through the get and remove methods of HashMap.

  • Method Details

    • getSubManager

      <T> T getSubManager(String manager, Class<? extends T> type)
      Retrieves a specific Manager from subManagers.
      Type Parameters:
      T - Any class that extends Manager
      Parameters:
      manager - The key value that maps to the desired Manager, typically its instance name
      type - The expected class of the desired Manager
      Returns:
      The Manager instance stored in subManagers

    • saveManagers

      void saveManagers()
      Persists all Manager in #subManagers to their data files.

    • shutdown

      void shutdown()
      This method is called when the option to 'quit' is selected.

      The method shutdown() should initiate all necessary data persistence procedures.
